1 olive oil
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
1 packet garlic paste
1 tin tomato sugo
1 packet Fresh Fettuccine
1 pear
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 pinch chilli flakes
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 4 mins
• Add seasoning, stock, garlic paste, tomato sugo and 1/2 the Parmesan and a splash of water. Stir through until heated. Season.

• Pour boiling water into a saucepan over high heat. Return to boil
• Cook fettuccine in boiling water until ‘al dente’, 3 mins
• Drain and return to pan with a drizzle of oil. Season.

• Slice pear
• In a bowl, combine pear, mixed
leaves and dressing. Season
• Divide fettuccine between plates.
Top with beef and tomato sugo
• Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan
and a pinch of chilli flakes (if using)
• Serve with pear salad